installing docker-compose - a cmdline tool that helps run docker in a easier way

1. install curl
    sudo apt-get install curl

2. install docker compose 
    curl -L https://github.com/docker/compose/releases/download/1.4.2/docker-compose-Linux-x86_64 > ~/Downloads/docker-compose

3. make it executable
    chmod +x ~/Downloads/docker-compose

4. put it in your system path
    sudo mv ~/Download/docker-compose /usr/local/bin

5. verify you can access it
    docker-compose --version


